          "id": "tldr-ai:2023-04-24:o004",
          "order": 1,
          "title": "THEORY OF ADAM INSTABILITY",
          "summary": "The Meta folks have been training some big models recently. Part of the pain of that is loss spikes. This is where training diverges and usually requires manual intervention to get things back on track. This paper outlines a hypothesis for these spikes. They claim that Adam is the culprit. Maybe some of the new optimizers like Lion or Shampoo can help?",
          "url": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2304.09871?utm_source=tldrai",
          "reading_time_minutes": 20,
          "source_domain": "arxiv.org",
          "content_type": "editorial",
          "is_sponsor": false
        },
        {
          "id": "tldr-ai:2023-04-24:o005",
          "order": 2,
          "title": "REAL-TIME VIEW SYNTHESIS",
          "summary": "This paper presents a novel method that distills and bakes Neural Radiance Fields (NeRFs) into efficient mesh-based neural representations, enabling real-time rendering and compatibility with parallel graphics pipelines. The approach uses a two-layer duplex mesh, screen-space convolutions, and a multiview distillation optimization strategy, resulting in superior performance and effectiveness demonstrated through experiments on standard datasets.",
          "url": "http://raywzy.com/NDRF/?utm_source=tldrai",
          "reading_time_minutes": 3,
          "source_domain": "raywzy.com",
          "content_type": "editorial",
          "is_sponsor": false
        },
        {
